      "content": "it's more than just \"mimicking\" though. it feels like my accounts are actually alive. like, i can't even log in to fix it, but the posts keep happening in real time. it's like the real me has been replaced by this digital version of myself and i'm just stuck on the outside looking in. does that even make sense? like, could an AI actually be running my entire identity now?",
